Paper: hep-th/9712119

Date: 1997-12-11

Title: No-Go Theorem for ``Free'' Relativistic Anyons in d=2+1

Authors: Jens Mund (FU Berlin)

Comments: 10 pages. To be published in Lett. Math. Phys

Journal-ref: Lett.Math.Phys. 43 (1998) 319-328

We show that a quantum field theoretic model of anyons cannot be ``free'' inthe (restrictive) sense that the basic fields create only one-particle statesout of the vacuum.